                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Signor <persName
                            type="to">Carignani</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-07-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 687.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 15th instant reporting the lynching of two Italians named
                    Giovanni and Vincenzo Serio, and the wounding of a third, named Salvatore
                    Liberto, by an armed mob at Erwin, Miss.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to say that the case has been at once referred to the
                    governor of Mississippi for appropriate action.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
